# Simple Moving Average (SMA) of Room_price_per_day_SG$

window_size = 5  # Adjust the window size as needed
sma = average_price_monthly_df['Room_price_per_day_SG$'].rolling(window=window_size).mean()

# Plotting the original and smoothed data
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 5))
plt.plot(average_price_monthly_df['Room_price_per_day_SG$'], label='Original')
plt.plot(sma, label=f'SMA ({window_size} months)')
plt.title('Room Prices Over 2010-2019 using Simple Moving Average')
plt.xlabel('Date of Booking')
plt.ylabel('Room_price_per_day_SG$')
plt.legend()
plt.show()

simple moving average for 5 months shows the data set with less noise¶

Decomposition¶

It appears that the overall trend indicates an increase in the price per room per day, even though a significant drop between 2014 and 2015. Following 2019, there seems to be a gradual decline once again. Also there are clear seasonalities in the chart¶

III. Testing for stationarit¶

In [274]:
## dickey_fuller test for smoothned data

from statsmodels.tsa.stattools import adfuller

result = adfuller(sma)  # Perform the test on the SMA series
print("ADF Statistic:", result[0])
print("p-value:", result[1])
print("Critical Values:", result[4])

ADF Statistic: -2.6545162548605488
p-value: 0.08224500896415199
Critical Values: {'1%': -3.4996365338407074, '5%': -2.8918307730370025, '10%': -2.5829283377617176}
¶

ADF Statistic: -2.6545162548605488 In this case, the value of the statistic is negative, indicating that the data might be stationary

Critical Values: {'1%': -3.4996365338407074, '5%': -2.8918307730370025, '10%': -2.5829283377617176} ADF statistic is more negative than these critical values, therefore the null hypothesis can reject with the corresponding level of confidence. But here ADF statistic is not more negative than the critical values at the typical significance levels..

Here data can be concluded as not stationary¶

In [275]:
# Check out a plot of autocorrelations

from statsmodels.graphics.tsaplots import plot_acf, plot_pacf # import the autocorrelation and partial correlation plots

plot_acf(sma)
plt.show()
around 33% of all data are outside the significant area, firther stationarisation needs for data set¶
